A vast cosmic cloudscape at dawn, rendered in Studio Ghibli style, showing thousands of tiny glowing firefly-like spheres swarming and reorganizing themselves across a twilight sky. Some spheres fade out while others instantly spark to life, creating a living, breathing constellation. Below, an ancient monolithic stone server tower crumbles peacefully into moss and wildflowers, while the luminous swarm above forms fluid, ever-shifting patterns like starlings in murmuration. Soft pink and gold morning light breaks through layered cumulus clouds, casting warm rays across the scene. The atmosphere is hopeful and transformative, capturing the moment between an old rigid world dissolving and a new adaptive one emerging. Delicate wisps of cloud trail between the floating spheres like silk threads connecting them in an invisible network. The color palette blends deep indigo shadows with warm amber highlights and soft seafoam greens.
